{
  "texts": [
    "We explain in some detail the reasoning at t 2 below.",
    "The adjudicator uses its Domain_Knowledge, which contains general rules for the situation, such as how to prioritize the beliefs of each agent and the definitions of negative and 0 belief in this context.",
    "When combined with the percepts reported by the ARCADIA Agents (IDCEC_KB_at_t2), ShadowAdjudicator is able to use IDCEC inference schemata to derive the current threat level.",
    "More formally, where this notation is simply \"pretty printed\" from underlying code, the situation is as follows:",
    "∀t: ∀a: ¬P(a, t, ¬φ) ∧ ¬P(a, t, φ) ⇒ B 0 (a, t, φ)} IDCEC_KB_at_t2 ={¬P(hdrone, t 0, ¬p), ¬P(hdrone, t 0, p), ¬P(ldrone, t 1, ¬p), ¬P(ldrone, t 1, p)"
  ]
}